<taxonomicName box="[1220,1322,373,406]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="236" pageNumber="515" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Mimosa</taxonomicName>
albida, 
<taxonomicName box="[227,356,420,445]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="236" pageNumber="515" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
) maintained by mist condensation at elevations of 280-980 m. The Coastal 
<taxonomicName authority="Mouse" authorityName="Mouse" box="[209,404,451,484]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Vesper" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="236" pageNumber="515" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Vesper Mouse</taxonomicName>
is only known from “Lomas” (mist oases) vegetation in southern Peru.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[179,1290,491,524]" pageId="236" pageNumber="515" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="236.[176,1386,294,920]" box="[179,1290,491,524]" pageId="236" pageNumber="515">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[179,440,491,524]" pageId="236" pageNumber="515">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
The Coastal 
<taxonomicName authority="Mouse" authorityName="Mouse" box="[627,823,491,524]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Vesper" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="236" pageNumber="515" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Vesper Mouse</taxonomicName>
is insectivorous and granivorous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
