<subSubSection pageId="236" pageNumber="515" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="236.[176,1386,294,920]" pageId="236" pageNumber="515">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[179,535,652,681]" pageId="236" pageNumber="515">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The IUCN Red List. Although common in habitats it occupies, the Coastal 
<taxonomicName authority="Mouse" authorityName="Mouse" box="[624,820,688,721]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Vesper" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="236" pageNumber="515" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Vesper Mouse</taxonomicName>
is endemic to a unique habitat type, the Lomas, which is heavily impacted by human activities, and might warrant some level of conservation protection in the future.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
